name: WeakRef()
return_value: A new WeakRef object referring to the given target value.

parameters.name: target
parameters.description: The target value the WeakRef should refer to (also called the referent). Must be an object or a non-registered symbol.

parameters.name: TypeError
parameters.description: Thrown if target is not an object or a non-registered symbol.

name: WeakRef.prototype.constructor
description: The constructor function that created the instance object. For WeakRef instances, the initial value is the WeakRef constructor.

name: WeakRef.prototype[@@toStringTag]
description: The initial value of the @@toStringTag property is the string "WeakRef". This property is used in Object.prototype.toString().

name: WeakRef.prototype.deref()
description: Returns the WeakRef object's target object, or undefined if the target object has been reclaimed.
return_value: The target value of the WeakRef, which is either an object or a non-registered symbol. Returns undefined if the value has been garbage-collected.
